{
  "texts": [
    "Models pretrained using either or both of the pretext tasks outperformed the baseline.",
    "Interestingly, the authors did not compare sequential pretraining with simultaneous optimization of both objectives using separate decoder heads.",
    "Huang et al. [126] also applied their method (see previous paragraph) to the downstream task of white matter segmentation on the publicly available WMH dataset [141], but did not compare with a fully supervised baseline.Studies have witnessed performance gains for other brain MRI tasks, such as brain anatomy segmentation [142][143][144], multiple sclerosis lesion segmentation [135,143], and stroke lesion segmentation [143].",
    "For instance, in an effort to improve brain anatomy segmentation, Chang et al.",
    "pretrained to solve two pretext tasks: (1) predicting the location of the vocal in the nearest supervoxel and (2) predicting the deformation field between the current volume and an atlas."
  ]
}